Mamelodi Sundowns boss Patrice Motsepe holds a media briefing on the latest developments at the football club. JOHANNESBURG - Mamelodi Sundowns boss Patrice Motsepe holds a media briefing on the latest developments at the football club. The Premier Soccer League season has been suspended until further notice due to the COVID-19 outbreak. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.